---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title="About — Andrew Vieau"
			description="I'm a technical trainer at Sitecore based in Big Lake, Minnesota."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>About</h1>

			<p>
				I work as a technical trainer at Sitecore, which means I spend most of my time helping
				people understand technology they just inherited or just bought. That sounds narrow, but it
				covers a lot of ground — architecture reviews, curriculum design, hands-on workshops,
				sometimes just sitting with someone while they figure out why something isn't working.
			</p>

			<p>
				I've been in enterprise tech for about a decade. Along the way I've done most of the jobs
				in the room at some point: developer, solution consultant, content strategist, learning
				experience designer. The training work came later and turned out to fit well, because I
				like explaining things.
			</p>

			<p>
				I'm based in Big Lake, Minnesota.
			</p>

			<p>
				This site is where I write about what I'm figuring out. Lately that's been Sitecore
				workflows, AI tools, and learning web development properly. I'm building this in Astro.
			</p>

			<p>
				You can find me on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrewvieau/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a>,
				<a href="https://github.com/andrewvieau/" target="_blank">GitHub</a>,
				<a href="https://roomwithavieau.bsky.social/" target="_blank">Bluesky</a>, and
				<a href="https://www.youtube.com/@andrewvieau" target="_blank">YouTube</a>.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
